==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sothic
<hw>Soth"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to <persfn>Sothis</persfn>,
the Egyptian name for the Dog Star; taking its name from the Dog Star;
canicular.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Sothiac year</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Sothic
year</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Chronol.)</fld>, <cd>the Egyptian year of
365 days and 6 hours, as distinguished from the Egyptian <xex>vague
year</xex>, which contained 365 days. The <xex>Sothic period</xex>
consists of 1,460 Sothic years, being equal to 1,461 vague years. One of
these periods ended in July, <sc>a. d.</sc> 139.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sotilte</ent>⟦br⟧
